I would say I like the anime about as much as i'm enjoying frieren, I get it people can only apparently so many fantasy anime at once but I do wish people would give it a chance!
anyways this has been my ramble about a anime no one is watching and the light novel I tried to read since it's based off it.

its annoying cause you see how it could have been really good with bits of action thrown in to have a nice mix of fighting to survive but also finding good people who are willing to help you. 
maybe the rest of the books get better? I probably wont be finding out. 
i'll keep up with the anime though

all that being said, I am enjoying the show, based on pacing i figure this season will end where vol 2 ended. this is about as far as I read and even that was a slog. 
vol 3 seems to be focusing on the fact that it want to indulge in that fav fantasy trope that begins with S and ends with lavery

it feels very "oh right i need to explain this" and also very "i don't want to put a 9 year old in actual danger even though she is being hunted" 
the anime makes that hunting more of a threat unlike the book where the town kind of falls offpage due to something else.

ok i'm being a little unfair, lots of things do happen but it's mostly off page. 
she changes her identity in ep one of the anime but we dont find out till she hits the first town in the book. 
the insert of the second book names ceil but we dont see that till near the end

I'll be honest when i saw the first volume had like... 68 chapters i was shocked. 
such each chapter was only a minute long but like... that made it great for being a tiny break inbetween tasks but I noticed quickly the problem with such short chapters.... nothing really happens

now normally I do wait till the end of a season to start reading the books but for whatever reason i didn't wnt to this time.
Now I am facing something i haven't really ever come across... at least not to this extent. 
see....
the anime is so much better then the novel?

So i've been watching a show this season called "the weakest tamer began a journey to pick up trash" 
it's really cute and well animated and i'm surprised i havent seen anyone talk about it.

if I were in a small town with no transit or taxi? i would drive... but i live 5 mins from a bus hub... 
*sighs* oh well! just going to keep working on the anxiety for now~

one day i'd love to be able to drive without fear, I know i'm not a bad driver I just can't handle other people on the road... 
but i sure don't want to be bullied into driving cause it's something adults need to do. 
I wish people would just be a little more understanding.

Thank you it is really reassuring to hear this opinion. especially since even in a world where I could, we only have space for two cars so I'd still be walking.
But yeah as I get older people get more judgmental about it but I'd rather be a safe pedestrian then a nervous/panicking driver.

again I know he was trying to be helpful but yeah it's just like... maybe some people are not able to drive... maybe i'll be fine later in life... it's really my choice alone on the matter. 
not everyone needs to drive?

"It really opens up your world" 
"I... know?" like... i'm the one who has to walk or bus or if it's really far taxi everywhere. I know i'm inconveniencing myself but pretty sure it's bad to be having panic attacks in a moving vehicle? 
like i already feel shitty enough for not being able to drive??

"Have you tried?" he asked. 
kinda annoyed to explain myself to barely above a stranger. "Yep, it didn't go well... I didn't crash but i did have a panic attack and nearly pass out so I decided at least for now... not for me"

I know people are well meaning... 
but today when i picked up my bro one of the other parents was like "will you be walking next week?" when it's supposed to be really cold. 
"I don't have much of a choice, no license" ha ha ha
